followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2016-01-25T17:13:45Z","updated_at":"2016-01-25T17:13:45Z","body":"@Darkyenus The only issue that comes to mind with that approach is that the Graphics object isn't describing a \"window\" specifically... per se. It does in desktop environments in certain cases.\n\nIt might be more consistent API wise to keep configuration options for the window in the `setWindowedMode` method.\n\nWhat would be even better is if we could also have a an enum, maybe `WindowProperty` that could be passed in as a varargs:\n\n`setWindowedMode(int, int, WindowProperty...)`\n\nso a call might be:\n\n`setWindowedMode(width, height, WIndowProperty.RESIZABLE, WindowProperty.DECORATED);`\n\nWhat do you think?\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/174589684/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"bgroenks96","id":841306,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg0MTMwNg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/841306?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgroenks96","html_url":"https://github.com/bgroenks96","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bgro